# ============================================================================
# Frontend Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env for local development
# For production, set these in AWS Amplify Console environment variables
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API Gateway URL (REQUIRED)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The base URL for the backend API Gateway endpoint.
# All API requests from the frontend will be sent to this URL.
#
# For local development:
# - Use http://localhost:3000 when running backend with serverless-offline
# - The backend must be running: cd backend && npm run dev
#
# For production (AWS Amplify):
# - Use your deployed API Gateway URL
# - Format: https://{api-id}.execute-api.{region}.amazonaws.com/{stage}
# - Example: https://abc123xyz.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod
#
# How to find your API Gateway URL after deployment:
# 1. Deploy backend: cd backend && npm run deploy
# 2. Look for "endpoints:" in the deployment output
# 3. Copy the URL (it will look like the example above)
# 4. Set this value in AWS Amplify Console (see instructions below)
#
# Important: All Vite environment variables must be prefixed with VITE_
# to be exposed to the client-side code.
VITE_API_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ============================================================================
# AWS Amplify Console Configuration (Production Deployment)
# ============================================================================
#
# For production deployments, environment variables should be configured in
# the AWS Amplify Console, NOT in a .env file.
#
# Setup Instructions:
#
# 1. Navigate to AWS Amplify Console:
#    https://console.aws.amazon.com/amplify/
#
# 2. Select your app (icon-set-generator)
#
# 3. Go to "App settings" > "Environment variables"
#
# 4. Add the following environment variable:
#    Key: VITE_API_GATEWAY_URL
#    Value: https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod
#
# 5. Save and redeploy your app
#
# Benefits of using Amplify Console environment variables:
# - Different values for different branches (dev, staging, prod)
# - No secrets in source code
# - Easy updates without code changes
# - Automatic injection during build process
#
# Branch-specific Configuration:
# You can set different values for different Git branches:
# - main branch: production API Gateway URL
# - develop branch: staging API Gateway URL
# - feature branches: development API Gateway URL
#
# To set branch-specific variables:
# 1. In Amplify Console, go to "App settings" > "Environment variables"
# 2. Click "Manage variables"
# 3. For each variable, click "Actions" > "Manage variable overrides"
# 4. Set different values for different branches
#
# ============================================================================
#
# Local Development Workflow:
#
# 1. Start backend locally:
#    cd backend
#    npm run dev
#    # Backend runs on http://localhost:3000
#
# 2. Create frontend/.env (copy from .env.example):
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Ensure VITE_API_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# 3. Start frontend:
#    cd frontend
#    npm run dev
#    # Frontend runs on http://localhost:5173
#
# 4. Test the integration:
#    - Open http://localhost:5173 in your browser
#    - Frontend will make API calls to http://localhost:3000
#
# ============================================================================
